JOHANNESBURG Two men, aged 28 and 54, were arrested and charged for dealing drugs after they were found with Mandrax tablets valued at R475,000 in Lavender Hill, police said in a statement on Monday.Police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Andr Traut said the arrest was made Sunday evening during a Public Order Police unit operation in Hillview in Lavender Hill.READ: Mandrax found inside teddy bear The search led police to the backyard where a steel trunk buried in the ground was found, comprising 8,990 mandrax tablets with a street value of R 475,000. Traut said the men are due to make a court appearance in Muizenberg on Tuesday.African News Agency